title: Nikki Haley
deleted: After Haley became U.S. ambassador to the United Nations, multiple pundits opined that she could become a possible Republican presidential candidate in the future<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/americas/100570367/nikki-haley-for-us-president-un-diplomats-bet-trump-envoy-has-ambitions |title= Nikki Haley for US president? | work =Stuff | place = Fairfax |date= January 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Adelman|first=Jonathan|title=Is 'Madame President' in Nikki Haley's Future? |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/is-madame-president-in-nikki-haleys-future_us_5a41c049e4b0df0de8b066bb|access-date=February 15, 2018| work = Huffington Post |date= December 25, 2017}}</ref> and could, in fact, win the White House.<ref>{{cite news |last=DeBellis|first=Lauren|title= Will Nikki Haley be America's first female president?|url=http://www.foxnews.com/opinion/2017/12/29/will-nikki-haley-be-americas-first-female-president.html |access-date=February 15, 2018 | work =Fox News|date=December 29, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kwong|first= Jessica |title=First Female President: Nikki Haley, Not Hillary Clinton, May Get that Honor, Says Fox Military Analyst|url=http://www.newsweek.com/first-female-president-nikki-haley-not-hillary-clinton-may-get-honor-says-fox-756901 |access-date=February 15, 2018| work = Newsweek |date= December 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shlufman|first= Dan|title=I'm with her: Why Nikki Haley may be the first female president |url=http://blogs.timesofisrael.com/im-with-her-why-nikki-haley-may-be-the-first-female-president/ |access-date=February 15, 2018 | work =Jewish Standard|date=January 5, 2018}}</ref> Trump was said by his staff to be grooming her in October 2017 for a national political role, having many private meetings with her on [[Air Force One]] after she had befriended his daughter, [[Ivanka Trump|Ivanka]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Wolff|first=Michael|date=2018|title=Fire and Fury: Inside the Trump White House|location= London |publisher=Little, Brown |pages=305â€“06|isbn=978-1-4087-1139-2|title-link=Fire and Fury}}</ref>

Rumors circulating since 2018 among many Republican Party officials as well as some Democrats and those in the media have theorized that Haley could run for president in [[2024 United States presidential election|2024]],<ref>{{cite news | via = You tube |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1LMjj9cPlWU |title= Nikki Haley eyeing 2024 election? |date=October 9, 2018 |access-date=October 9, 2018}}</ref> with some saying she would be a viable candidate for the Republicans and a tough opponent for Democrats.<ref>{{cite news | via = You tube |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pEKrZfRWX2I |title=Jessica Tarlov: Nikki Haley could be the first female president |date=June 12, 2018 |access-date=June 12, 2018}}</ref>  In 2020, Haley ranked first in the ten women most likely to be the first female president by an op-ed on ''[[The Washington Post]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title= The 10 women most likely to be the first female president|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/03/27/10-women-most-likely-be-first-female-president/}}</ref>
